The ability of HDMI singal Up & Down Scaling is a crucial function when working with 1080P or 4K sources in a complex AV system and distributing the HDMI source to multiple displays which have varying resolution support.  Device incorporates two output modes,  bypass mode (input folows output) - device read and mix all source and displays EDID information ,output the highest resolution that all source and displays support.  scaler mode - device reads and analyzes the EDID information from two displays simultaneously,realize the handshake of displays individually,output the highest supported resolution between source and displays,ensuring maximum compatibility in any system.When user upgrade 4K display in the AV system ,device would be used as HDMI up-scaler,automatically integrate a 1080P@24/25/30Hz source into 4K x 2K at corresponding refresh rate.When user upgrade 4K source in the AV system, device would be used as HDMI down-scaler,automatically integrate a 4K2K@24/25/30 source into 1080P at corresponding refresh rate.In scaler mode,make sure that the HDMI output of your source defaults to or can be set to refresh rate at 24/25/30 Hz    Feature  Compliant with HDMI 1.4, HDCP 1.4 and backword compliant with DVI 1.0  Port1 is built in an HDMI / MHL dual-input interface,compliant with MHL 2.0  Clock Rate up to 25MHz- 300Mhz, Maximum Bandwidth is 9Gbps  Simultaneous HDMI outputs  Support standard audio, DSD audio and HD audio (HBR);  Support CEC treatment protocol;  Incorporate two output modes,one of which is,and the second is Scaler  In bypass mode - Support 1080P@60Hz,,3D,4096¡Á2160p@24 Hz and 3840¡Á2160p@24/25/30 Hz resolution output

DMS-59 system interface is the standard for connecting both digital and analog monitors to low-profile PCI and AGP graphic cards,features the LFH (Low Force Helix) contacts, and has become the industry-wide standard for all multi-head monitor graphic card applications, regardless of form factor.The DMS-59 meets VESA requirements for impedance, cross-talk and skew.  Based on the 60-circuit LFH, the DMS-59 uses a voided pin (circuit #58) as the keying mechanism. This connector system consists of a 59-circuit receptacle, plug and eight cable assembly configurations.Coboc offer the most popular ones - DMS-59 to Dual VGA & DMS-59 to Dual DVI-I adapter cables    This DMS 59 to dual VGA Y cable allows you to break out one LFH 59 or LFH 60 (DMS 59 and DMS 60) connection into two VGA(HDB15) female connectors, letting you connect two VGA monitors for a cost-effective dual display solution.  Compatible with most DMS-59 video cards including NVidia, Matrox, HP, PNY, and ATI  Attach two VGA enabled monitors to your DMS59 Graphics card  Plug and play, dual display setup
